# Portfolio Website

This repository contains the code for my personal **Portfolio Website**, showcasing my projects, skills, and professional experience. It includes an Index/Home page, About Me page, Work (projects) page, and Contact Me page.

---

## Table of Contents

1. [Project Overview](#project-overview)
2. [Features](#features)
3. [Technologies Used](#technologies-used)
4. [Setup and Installation](#setup-and-installation)
5. [Usage](#usage)
6. [Author](#author)

---

## Project Overview

The **Portfolio Website** is a responsive and interactive web application designed to highlight who I am and what I do. Visitors can learn about me, browse my project gallery, and get in touch via the contact form.

---

## Features

- **Project Gallery**  
  A gallery displaying my projects with descriptions and direct links to each GitHub repository.
- **Responsive Design**  
  Optimized layout for mobile, tablet, and desktop screens.
- **Contact Form**  
  A simple form for visitors to send me messages.

---

## Technologies Used

- **HTML5** – Structure and content
- **CSS3** – Styling and responsive layout
- **JavaScript** – Interactive functionality
- **CSS Animations with SVG**
- **SCSS** (https://www.sassmeister.com/)
- **Transpiler** (https://madlittlemods.github.io/- - -
  postcss-css-variables/playground/)
- **Using Auto Prefixers** (https://- autoprefixer.github.io/)

---

## Setup and Installation

To set up and run the Portfolio Website locally, follow these steps:

1. **Clone the repository**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/hostech83/Portfolio-website.git
   cd Portfolio-website
   Usage
   Visit the website in your browser to explore the portfolio.
   ```

Navigate through the sections: Work, About Me, and Contact.

Use the contact form to send a message or follow links to my social media and GitHub profiles.

